{
  "text": "Reference trees were used to identify the trees in Tomakomai. Fifty Q. dentata reference trees were arbitrarily selected from its pure stand in Nakaotofuke (43°07 0 N, 143°05 0 E), and 50 Q. crispula trees were selected from each of its pure stands in Hamamasu (43°35 0 N, 141°28 0 E) and Toishiyama (43°00 0 N, 141°17 0 E). Leaf morphology of these Q. dentata and Q. crispula reference trees has already been reported by [CITATION_1] . Reference trees of Q. serrata were obtained from a mixed stand of Q. crispula and Q. serrata in Aoba Park (43°00 0 N, 141°30 0 E), because no pure stand of Q. serrata was found in Hokkaido; 30 trees having Q. serrata characteristics were selected. Leaves, acorns, and insects were collected from 2005 to 2008 except for reference trees of Q. dentata and Q. crispula, which were examined in 1999 [CITATION_2] ).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "22592739",
    "[CITATION_2]": "22592739"
